WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Heat hits us harder. In summer, it can actually move your numbers.

00:07.000 --> 00:17.000
Heat and high sugar both pull water from you. With less water, the glucose gets more concentrated — sugar climbs, and you lose even more. A loop that builds fast.

00:17.000 --> 00:25.000
Thirst is a late signal. By the time you feel it, you're already behind — and with neuropathy, even quieter.

00:25.000 --> 00:33.000
Heat is hard on your gear, too. Insulin and test strips have temperature limits — a hot car or sunny bag can ruin them.

00:33.000 --> 00:42.000
So make water the default. Keep it within arm's reach and sip through the day — don't wait for thirst. Skip the sugary and energy drinks.

00:42.000 --> 00:51.000
On hot days, check your sugar a little more often. And keep your insulin and meter out of the heat — never a hot car or direct sun.

00:51.000 --> 00:59.000
Diabetes is a 24/7 job. You don't have to carry it alone.

00:59.000 --> 01:06.000
LocalDiabetic. We just help you carry the day. Win big.
